        <div id="post" id='post-15397'> 
        <h2 class="c_title"><a href="http://www.ingredientsinc.net/2010/12/cozy-up-with-peppermint-hot-chocolate/" title="Cozy Up with Peppermint Hot Chocolate">Cozy Up with Peppermint Hot Chocolate</a></h2>
       
       
        <span class="date">December 12, 2010<br /></span>
        
        
        <p id="content"><h3><a onclick="javascript:pageTracker._trackPageview('/outgoing/www.ingredientsinc.net/wp-content/uploads/2010/12/IMG_92863.jpg');"  href="http://www.ingredientsinc.net/wp-content/uploads/2010/12/IMG_92863.jpg"><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-15424" title="IMG_9286" src="http://www.ingredientsinc.net/wp-content/uploads/2010/12/IMG_92863.jpg" alt="" width="320" height="397" /></a></h3>
<h3>It has been so cold outside lately, so my kids have been requesting hot chocolate. Since I had some peppermint sticks on hand, I crushed them up and made this really simple Peppermint Hot Chocolate mixture. They were ecstatic, and this has been a weekly beverage. I used skim milk in my recipe because that is what we drink at my house to reduce the calories and fat a bit. Enjoy this cozy beverage just in time for the holidays.</h3>
</p>
        <div class="hrecipe">
        <h2 class="fn">Peppermint Hot Chocolate</h2>
            <img width="322" height="400" src="http://www.ingredientsinc.net/wp-content/uploads/2010/12/IMG_9286.jpg" class="photo wp-post-image" alt="IMG_9286" title="IMG_9286" style="display: none;" /><div>
    <span class="contant_c">Prep:</span>
    <span class="main_contant_c preptime">	    <span class="value-title" title="PT5M"></span>5 minutes</span>
</div><div>
    <span class="contant_c">Cook:</span>
    <span class="main_contant_c cooktime"><span class="value-title" title="PT10M"></span>10 minutes</span>
</div><div>
    <span class="contant_c">Yield:</span>
    <span class="main_contant_c yield">4 servings</span>
</div><div class="content_header">Ingredients</div>
<div class="main_contant_c"><span class="ingredient"><span class="amount">1/3  cup</span> <span class="name"> unsweetened cocoa powder</span></span><br />
<span class="ingredient"><span class="amount">1</span> <span class="name">quart skim milk</span></span><br />
<span class="ingredient"><span class="amount">1/2  cup</span> <span class="name"> semisweet chocolate chips</span></span><br />
<span class="ingredient"><span class="amount">4</span> <span class="name">regular-size peppermint sticks, crushed</span></span><br />
<span class="ingredient"><span class="amount">1  cup</span> <span class="name"> mini marshmallows</span></span><br />
<span class="ingredient"><span class="amount" style="position: absolute; width: 1px; height: 1px; clip: auto; overflow: hidden;">1</span> <span class="name">Peppermint sticks (optional)</span></span></div><div class="content_header">Preparation</div>
<div class="main_contant_c instructions">1 Place cocoa in a medium saucepan. Gradually whisk in milk until cocoa has dissolved. Add chocolate chips and crushed peppermint; simmer over medium heat, stirring occasionally, until chocolate and peppermint have melted, 8 to 10 minutes.<br />
<br />
2. Bring to a boil and immediately remove from heat. Ladle into mugs and top with mini marshmallows. Serve each with peppermint sticks, if desired.</div>		</div>
        
   
        
